[4] Regional updates: ProMED SoAs
[A] Bangladesh
Date: Fri 6 Aug 2021 12.00 AM BST
Source: The Daily Star [edited]
https://www.thedailystar.net/health/disease/coronavirus/news/country-hits-another-grim-milestone-2145831


The country yesterday [5 Aug 2021] recorded the highest number of COVID-19 deaths in a single day. A total of 264 people died in 24 hours ending at 8:00 am yesterday [5 Aug 2021], read a press release of the Directorate General of Health Services (DGHS).

Earlier, the record was 258 deaths on [27 Jul 2021]. The total number of COVID-19 deaths in the country now stands at 21 902 and the COVID-19 death rate stands at 1.66%.

As the country's healthcare system grapples with the wave of COVID-19 cases caused largely by the delta variant, 12 744 new cases were reported yesterday [5 Aug 2021]. A total of 46 995 samples were tested across the country during the 24-hour period. Yesterday's [5 Aug 2021] positivity rate was 27.12%.

So far 1 322 654 COVID cases have been detected since the first cases were reported on [8 Mar 2020]. In the last 15 days, 186 151 people tested positive for COVID-19 in the country.

Among yesterday's [5 Aug 2021] 264 deceased, 124 were women. Of the dead, one was under 10 years old, one was between 11 and 20 years old, 5 were between 21 and 30 years, 25 between 31 and 40 years, 31 between 41 and 50 years, 59 between 51 and 60 years, 74 between 61 and 70 years, 50 between 71 and 80 years, 15 between 81 and 90 years, and 3 between 91 and 100 years old, added the release.

According to the DGHS, 1647 people died between Friday [30 Jul 2021] and yesterday [5 Aug 2021]. In the previous week, 1570 people had died from COVID-19.

At least 15 786 COVID-19 patients were registered recovered yesterday [5 Aug 2021]. The total number of recoveries now stands at 1 156 943 and the recovery rate at 87.47%. The ongoing lockdown has been extended to [10 Aug 2021] to curb transmission.

