[B] India
Date: Fri 6 Aug 2021 11:09 AM IST
Source: Yahoo News, Press Trust of India (PTI) report [abridged, edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/coronavirus


India saw a single day rise of 44 643 new coronavirus infections taking the total tally of COVID-19 cases to 31 856 757, while the active cases registered an increase for the 3rd consecutive day, according to the Union Health Ministry data updated on Friday [6 Aug 2021].

The death toll climbed to 426 754 with 464 fresh fatalities. The active cases comprise 1.30% of the total infections, while the national COVID-19 recovery rate was recorded at 97.36%, the data updated at 8 am [6 Aug 2021] showed.

An increase of 3083 cases has been recorded in the active COVID-19 caseload in a span of 24 hours.

