[C] Nepal
Date: Thu 5 Aug 2021 04:50 PM NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [abridged, edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/covid-cases-rising-steadily-in-nepal-37-more-fatalities-take-death-toll-to-9994


Nepal reported 3007 fresh COVID-19 cases on [Thu 5 Aug 2021], while 931 people were detected to have been infected through antigen test, adding up to a total of 3938 single day infections. Following this, the coronavirus caseload has reached 708 079, as per the Ministry of Health and Population's records.

Meanwhile, the total coronavirus recoveries stand at 663 663 with 2012 discharges logged today [5 Aug 2021]. The countrywide COVID-19 mortality toll increased to 9994 with 37 more fatalities.

As per the latest data provided by the health ministry, 18 408 total tests were conducted in the last 24 hours of which 11 870 were PCR tests while 6538 were antigen tests. With this, a total of 3 656 342 PCR tests have been carried out to date [5 Aug 2021].

Nepal's COVID-19 recovery rate stands at 93.7%, while the fatality rate stands at 1.5%. The country's active COVID-19 case count currently is 34 422 as opposed to 33 464 on [Wed 4 Aug 2021]. As many as 766 infections surfaced in the capital today [5 Aug 2021] while Lalitpur and Bhaktapur recorded 163 and 146 respectively.

So far, a total of 6 490 177 people have received the coronavirus vaccine across the country, of which 4 359 277 have received the 1st dose while only 2 130 900 individuals have been inoculated with both the doses and are fully vaccinated. Currently, there are 375 individuals in various quarantine facilities across Nepal.

On [Wed 4 Aug 2021], Nepal's coronavirus case count had reached 705 072 with 2975 more people testing positive for the infection.

