[Data by country, area, or territory for 6 Aug 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20AUG6_1628365763.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 31.5% of daily case numbers and 34.4% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 78.11 million cases. The USA reported over 91 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by Brazil (40 716), Mexico (20 685), and Argentina (13 736). 9 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 24.6% of daily case numbers and 13.1% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 60.94 million cases. Many countries not reporting deaths in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (3 cases), Switzerland (4 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. 16 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 10 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 9.8% of daily case numbers and 6.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 12.94 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (38 674) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Libya, and UAE. Saudi Arabia, and Jordan, reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 5.4% of daily case numbers and 8.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.08 million cases. South Africa (13 646), reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours followed by Botswana, Zimbabwe, Algeria, Kenya, Mozambique, and Eswatini. Zambia, Ethiopia, Nigeria, Rwanda, and Malawi, reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Lesotho, Gabon, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 8.9% of daily case numbers and 8.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 4.78 million cases. Malaysia, reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 20 000 cases), followed by Japan, Philippines, Vietnam, South Korea, Mongolia, Fiji, and Cambodia.

- The South East Asia region reported 19.5% of the daily newly reported cases and 29.0% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 38.96 million cases. India is dominant reporting over 44 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Indonesia (39 532), Thailand (21 379), Bangladesh (12 606), Myanmar (3588), and Nepal (2430). Also, Sri Lanka and Maldives have not reported any cases for many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 6 Aug 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

